item.title: CVE-2018-4013|2024-08-05T05:04:28.266Z -- live%20networks -- live555%20media%20server
item.description: An exploitable code execution vulnerability exists in the HTTP packet-parsing functionality of the LIVE555 RTSP server library version 0.92. A specially crafted packet can cause a stack-based buffer overflow, resulting in code execution. An attacker can send a packet to trigger this vulnerability.
